OL,6,FIt means the business has been scammed
OL,7,Fof a total of #139.50.
OL,9,FLauren Evans, a Managing Director of
OL,10,FFablas, told ITV News that members of
OL,11,Fstaff had originally checked the
OL,12,FScottish notes with a pen checker and
OL,13,Fdue to the notes being so
OL,14,Fsophisticated, they had passed the
OL,15,Ftest of being real.
OL,17,FHowever it was only at the end of the
OL,18,Fday when the store was being cashed-up
OL,19,Fthat staff investigated in more detail
OL,20,Fon spotting the signs of a fake note.
